<item>
            <title>[JDK-8304884] Update Bytecodes data to be mostly compile time constants</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8304884</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>Bytescodes contains various arrays which are all effectively compile time constants, but are not defined as such. Instead the data is filled in by bytecodes_init() during VM initialization. We can make everything except _flags compile time constants easily by using some macros and C++14 constexpr. We can also ensure the bytecodes data is in the right order by asserting such in debug builds removing the reasoning for not making it a compile time constant in the first place.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
_flags might be able to be made compile time constant using some constexpr tricks, but that will not be tackled in this enhancement.</description>
